{"cursor":"5334","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox Museum |name = Ukrainian National Chornobyl Museum |native_name =\nÐ£ÐºÑÐ°ÑÐ½ÑÑÐºÐ¸Ð¹ Ð½Ð°ÑÑÐ¾Ð½Ð°Ð»ÑÐ½Ð¸Ð¹ Ð¼ÑÐ·ÐµÐ¹ \"Ð§Ð¾ÑÐ½Ð¾Ð±Ð¸Ð»Ñ\" |native_name_lang = ukr |image = Kiev-\nUkrainianNationalChernobylMuseum 02.jpg |imagesize = 300 |caption = The museum\nfacade and outdoor exhibition of liquidator vehicles |alt = |map_type = Ukraine\n|map_caption = Location within Ukraine |map_alt = Map of Ukraine |latitude =\n50.466389 |longitude = 30.517222 |established = |dissolved = |location =\nprovulok Khoryva, 1 (Ð¿ÑÐ¾Ð²ÑÐ». Ð¥Ð¾ÑÐ¸Ð²Ð°, 1), Kyiv, Ukraine |type = |collection =\n7000+ |visitors = |director = Ivan Gladush |curator = |publictransit =\nKontraktova Ploshcha Metro Station (); Tram Routes 12, 14, 18, 19 |website =\n[http://www.chornobylmuseum.kiev.ua/index.php?lang=en\nwww.chornobylmuseum.kiev.ua] }}\n\n\nThe 'Ukrainian National Chornobyl Museum' ({{lang-uk|Ð£ÐºÑÐ°ÑÐ½ÑÑÐºÐ¸Ð¹ Ð½Ð°ÑÑÐ¾Ð½Ð°Ð»ÑÐ½Ð¸Ð¹\nÐ¼ÑÐ·ÐµÐ¹ \"Ð§Ð¾ÑÐ½Ð¾Ð±Ð¸Ð»Ñ\"}}) is a history museum in Kiev, Ukraine, dedicated to the 1986\nChernobyl disaster and its consequences. It houses an extensive collection of\nvisual media, artifacts, scale models and other representational items designed\nto educate the public about many aspects of the disaster. Several exhibits\ndepict the technical progression of the accident, and there are also many areas\ndedicated to the loss of life and cultural ramifications of the disaster.\n\nDue to the nature of the subject material, the museum provides a very visually\nengaging experience.\n. To stress the tragedy of devastation, the signs are colored in black (instead\n  of standard blue/white) and slashed with pink stripe (which designates \"end of\n  the settlement\" on the actual signs). Above the signs is an authentic\n  [[Khorugv]] from the abandoned village church.]]\n\nMuseum occupies an early 20th-century building which formerly housed a fire\nbrigade and was donat